\providecommand*\caption@xref[2]{\@setref\relax\@undefined{#1}}
\newlabel{fig:architecture}{{1}{3}{STEM Agent architecture. Callers interact through the Standard Interface Layer, which routes requests through five protocol handlers (A2A, AG-UI, A2UI, UCP, AP2) to the Agent Core. The core's cognitive pipeline is supported by a four-type Memory System and the MCP Integration Layer (including the new \texttt {mcp-server} package that exposes the agent as MCP tools). The Agent Differentiation Layer provides the machinery---domain personas, skills, rules, and MCP configuration---that transforms the generic stem agent into domain-specific variants (e.g., FinanceAgent, SREAgent)}{figure.caption.1}{}}
